Et samarbejde med Nets. 

 

Ved oprettelse af en ny butik skal kunden selv søge et forretnings nr. (se spørgsmål neden for ) Det må vi ikke. Kan bestilles hos Nets på 30154460 

Det er vigtigt at vide at et forretningsnr. fra Nets er på 7 ciffer, og fra Worldline er på 8 ciffer. Vi kan kun søge TID hos Nets, for kunden. Det er ikke altid Nets kan se det ikke er deres kunde, så check lige en ekstra gang med kunden. 

 Fra 31-12-23 vil vi flytte alle Nets aftalerne over til Nets, startende med Sverige og Norge. 

Når vi for forretningsnummeret retur fra kunden kan vi søge et Terminal ID hos Nets. ( TID )

title: Contract termination - DK customers
text: When a customer decides to leave K3/DdD it is normally done through the ticket system in FreshDesk - Because the main page of K3 doesn't have any contact information to Finance. First Line will respond to the ticket with the follwing message. You have sent this message to technical support, unfortunately we cannot handle this type of enquiry. Please send it to finance.nordic@k3btg.com Then set status to Passed to Customer Success Manager. If you pass to a CSM, and they confirm that they have now taken over the request and are in contact with the customer, then you can resolve the ticket.
description:
When a customer decides to leave K3/DdD it is normally done through the ticket system in FreshDesk - Because the main page of K3 doesn't have any contact information to Finance.


First Line will respond to the ticket with the follwing message.

You have sent this message to technical support, unfortunately we cannot handle this type of enquiry.
Please send it to finance.nordic@k3btg.com


Then set status to Passed to Customer Success Manager.


If you pass to a CSM, and they confirm that they have now taken over the request and are in contact with the customer, then you can resolve the ticket.

title: After how many years hardware should be replaced
text: Approved by Carl Duffill 18Dec2023 Often customers contact us with old hardware. We should point them to the following recommendations to avoid having to provide support for obsolete equipment that should have been replaced long ago. Product We recommend replacement after K3 POS PC 5 years* Label printer Citizen CLP-521 3 years K3 Receipt printer 3 years Epson 88 or DdD Receipt printer These are all older than 3 years, we always recommend replacing them 1D Scanner (K3-2250) 3 years 2D Scanner with holder USB (K3-6600) 3 years 2D Wireless scanner (K3-2290) 3 years Terminal (Lane 3000) 3 years *If the POS is running with Windows 7, it is definitely older than 5 years

title: Issues with touchscreen
text: Whether the customer is unable to use the screen at all or if it behaves strangely, displaying zones where it seems like there is continuous tapping in a corner or other peculiar errors, it may primarily be due to the ELO driver not being installed. Check in the bottom right corner of the desktop if ELO is visible there. If not, search for ELO. If Windows doesn't find anything, the driver is not installed. Open https://www.elotouch.com/support/downloads#/ Choose Touch Driver and the Windows version they are using (check under System Information if needed) and ALWAYS choose the Single Touch Driver. Unzip the file. Choose the language (it is not available in Danish, so for Danish customers, choose English). Check the Serial option. Agree to the License Agreement. Check the option for it to automatically detect the screen. Usually, the screen is connected to COM5. If the PC cannot find a COM5, check if something is connected to, for example, COM7 (in this case, a scanner). Then choose COM4. Proceed with Next. The driver will be installed. Usually, the PC needs to be restarted when the installation is complete. After restart, check that ELO is installed. If the customer is on the line, they should assist you with the next step, where you need to calibrate the screen. Otherwise, call them after the installation and restart are finished. Right-click on ELO and select Align... Have the customer press on the target circles (there will be 3-4 of them in different corners), and then they should run their finger around the screen until the calibration is complete. Afterward, the screen should work with touch. If installation and calibration do not work, there may be an issue with the screen itself. It either needs testing or they need a replacement.
description:
Whether the customer is unable to use the screen at all or if it behaves strangely, displaying zones where it seems like there is continuous tapping in a corner or other peculiar errors, it may primarily be due to the ELO driver not being installed.


  1. Check in the bottom right corner of the desktop if ELO is visible there.


  2. If not, search for ELO.


  3. If Windows doesn't find anything, the driver is not installed.

  4. Open https://www.elotouch.com/support/downloads#/

  5. Choose Touch Driver and the Windows version they are using (check under System Information if needed) and ALWAYS choose the Single Touch Driver.


  6. Unzip the file.


  7. Choose the language (it is not available in Danish, so for Danish customers, choose English).


  8. Check the Serial option.


  9. Agree to the License Agreement.


  10. Check the option for it to automatically detect the screen.


  11. Usually, the screen is connected to COM5. If the PC cannot find a COM5, check if something is connected to, for example, COM7 (in this case, a scanner). Then choose COM4.


  12. Proceed with Next.


  13. The driver will be installed.


  14. Usually, the PC needs to be restarted when the installation is complete.


  15. After restart, check that ELO is installed.


  16. If the customer is on the line, they should assist you with the next step, where you need to calibrate the screen. Otherwise, call them after the installation and restart are finished.

  17. Right-click on ELO and select Align...


  18. Have the customer press on the target circles (there will be 3-4 of them in different corners), and then they should run their finger around the screen until the calibration is complete.


  19. Afterward, the screen should work with touch.

  20. If installation and calibration do not work, there may be an issue with the screen itself. It either needs testing or they need a replacement.

title: List over emails allowed for Backoffice password retrieval
text: If the customer wants to retrieve login information for Backoffice and he/she receives nothing when adding a specific email adresse, check if the address is added in DdD backoffice Support Tools. If not, add the email address and have them try again.
